From c0df7de60bb6fbd81041e7d1f7f157b05b194184 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nikolay Amiantov <ab@fmap.me>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 16:21:38 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Add Sony ARW6 (LLVC v3) lossy decoder

Reverse-engineered 'Compressed HQ' (Sony LLVC v3, raw SubIFD compression
32766) decompressor, ported from a prototype verified bit-exact against
the Adobe DNG Converter. Line-based inverse 5/3 wavelet pipeline with an
adaptive entropy coder, flipped vertical polyphase and a luma/chroma
combine; the per-band 16-byte header gives the entropy offset and
per-orientation quantizers. Adds BitStreamerMSB::byteAlign() and wires
compression 32766 into ArwDecoder.

The linearized output's black/white levels are in the codec curve's scale
(black 1024, white 32800), not the ARW SR2 14-bit scale: using the SR2
black (512) leaves a pedestal the white-balance gains turn into a magenta
cast. They override the camera-database / SR2-tag values for arw6. The
a7R VI's lower SONYWHITELEVEL (15360) is also skipped (keeps the camera
database white 16383) so lossless/uncompressed highlights match Adobe.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
