+    from a verified prototype (bit-exact against the Adobe oracle). The codec is
+    a line-based inverse-wavelet pipeline: per spatial-quadrant plane it decodes
+    four wavelet components -- A (luma low band, 4-level 2D 5/3 wavelet), B (luma
+    full-resolution highpass), and C, D (the two chroma difference bands) -- with
+    an adaptive entropy coder, a flipped 5/3 vertical lifting, and a Sony-specific
+    luma/chroma combine, then linearizes through a baked codec curve.
